# Kubernetes Rule — Deployment Standards

All deployable runtimes must follow platform deployment conventions.

## Deployment unit
Each deployment should be representable through a typed deployment spec.

## Standard Kubernetes resources
Prefer the following set:
- Deployment
- Service
- ConfigMap
- Secret reference
- Ingress or HTTPRoute
- HorizontalPodAutoscaler
- NetworkPolicy

## Metadata
All resources must include standard labels:
- app.kubernetes.io/name
- app.kubernetes.io/instance
- app.kubernetes.io/component
- app.kubernetes.io/managed-by
- platform.io/project-id
- platform.io/deployment-id
- platform.io/environment
- platform.io/tenant-id

## Container standards
- Expose a health endpoint
- Log to stdout/stderr
- Read config from env/config files
- Do not rely on writable local disk unless explicitly required

## Runtime profiles
Each deployment must support a runtime profile such as:
- small
- medium
- large

Runtime profile should control:
- replicas
- requests/limits
- autoscaling thresholds
- timeout defaults

## Release behavior
- Prefer rolling deployments first
- Canary/blue-green is a future enhancement unless explicitly requested

## Forbidden patterns
- Do not generate ad hoc kubectl shell scripts as primary deployment logic
- Do not hardcode cluster names or namespaces in application logic
- Do not embed infrastructure credentials in deployer code
